summary: antis are saying stuff like ‘emilia clearly didn’t understand her own character!’ and you guys do? when you look through the...
body:
antis are saying stuff like ‘emilia clearly didn’t understand her own character!’

and you guys do?

when you look through the eyes of that character for nearly 10 years you understand that character better than anyone

you live in their shoes 

antis don’t understand it because by being an anti i guarantee 90% of you refused to see where that character is coming and try to understand them just because they didn’t like them 

you can’t blame the actors for defending a character they spent a large chunk of their life as 

there is a special attachment you get by playing characters for this long and to not feel for them in any sort of way or understand their struggles etc. is blasphemy

also, emilia was one of the only people on the cast that actually read the books which mean not only does she understand her character more than most actors but also most of the audience who hasn’t read the books (likely including those complaining about it)

Queen of the Andals and the First Men
summary: The Breaker of Chains Was Broken.
body:
The Breaker of Chains Was Broken.

I love how no one is realizing dany was breaking way before the finale. Everyone was too busy cheering the breaker of chains and mother of dragons to notice everytime she lost someone she cracked a little each time.

First the years of physical and psychological abuse from Viserys. Then she is sold to drago is abused by him then she watches drago kill her brother and she pretty much develops Stockholm syndrome and forms a bond with him then loses him. With her loss of drogo she tries to burn herself with his body and emerges as the mother of dragons with Drogon, Viserion, and Rhaegal.Through out the seasons she loses more people and is betrayed by countless more who mean so much to her especially including losing Viserion and Rhaegal. Dany finally snaps when she watches Missandei die. She was a child fighting a war for her birthright not the mad queen following in her father’s footsteps

summary: Emilia Clarke’s complete and utter shock and despair at discovering Dany’s dark turn seems to be pretty telling as to what D&D...
body:
Emilia Clarke’s complete and utter shock and despair at discovering Dany’s dark turn seems to be pretty telling as to what D&D were trying to do. There are certain scenes that have been brought up to support her going mad, but a lot of them are tonally ambiguous. 

For example, while some have said the scene where she watches her brother die shows her darkness, but most saw that as her taking back her power from her abuser. 

And there are many more that others see in this way, because thats how Emilia was told to see it. No nuance. 

She grew so intimately with a character that she didn’t know anything about. From an acting standpoint, learning something this big and looking back on everything you would have done differently if you had known this has got to be excruciating. 

Telling Emilia could have gone a long way towards giving Dany the epic character arc she deserved, and the one I think we will find fascinating in the books.
